LAGOS – Lagos State Judiciary in partnership with the German Agency for In­ternational Corporation (GIZ)-SEDIN Programme is organizing a three-day peer learning and capaci­ty development workshop to strengthen the operation of the Small Claims Court in SEDIN’s partner states for enhanced and effective commercial dispute reso­lution system in the focal states. The workshop with the theme; “Strengthening the Operation of the Small Claims Court in GIZ-SE­DIN Partner States” had in attendance participants from SEDIN’s partner states. Hon. Justice Kazeem Alogba, Chief Judge, La­gos state Judiciary in his welcome remarks at the day one and opening of the workshop on Tuesday said the aim of the programme is to provide training for Chief Magistrates, Mag­istrates and other partici­pants in the operation of the Small Claims Court in GIZ-SEDIN Partner States. IBEDC Faults Oyo Government On Closure Of Offices Eguavoen, Amuneke Should Guard Against Clash Of Interest,… “I hope that the knowl­edge the participants ob­tain, and the skills and techniques participants develop here, in this pro­gramme, will enhance their abilities to excel and make good success in the operation and/or establish­ment of the Small Claims Court in their respective jurisdictions.